        - <span>SCHOLARS&#x2019; CHOICE: Part 1</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>1.</p>
    <p>Team­work is im­por­tant</p>
    <p>I worked with a di­verse team of doc­tors, nurses and al­lied health­care pro­fes­sion­als such as med­i­cal so­cial work­ers and psy­chol­o­gists. I got to be­friend col­leagues from other de­part­ments and learn about their spe­cial­i­ties.</p>
    <p>2.</p>
    <p>Don’t be afraid to ask for help</p>
    <p>I asked col­leagues to help with can­nu­la­tion (in­sert­ing a tube into the body) and draw­ing blood be­fore con­duct­ing swab tests. 3.</p>
    <p>Have more em­pa­thy</p>
    <p>I put my­self in my pa­tients’ shoes so I could al­lay their anx­i­eties be­fore per­form­ing the swab tests.</p>


